agency in an advertising market that is growing hot. By Stuart
Elliott.
</P>
<P>
   SCHWEPPES-BOTTLING (Undated) _ Cadbury Schweppes, the thinking
went, needed a big bottler in the United States to compete with the
distribution might of Coca-Cola and Pepsi. But Cadbury's bottler in
its first year has been plagued by problems. Plants have been
closed, and now, at the peak of the summer season, they are unable
to deliver products to several of their biggest customers. By
Constance L. Hays.
</P>
<P>
   AIRFARES-INTERNET (Undated) _ More about the recent promotions
by airlines offering discount fares over the Internet, and what
travel agents are doing. By Edwin McDowell.
</P>
<P>
   CZECH-MEDIA (Prague) _ When SBS Broadcasting signed a merger
agreement with Central European Media Enterprises in March, they
had hoped to become one of the most powerful media networks in
Central and Eastern Europe. But since then Central European Media
has become entangled in a dispute that could result in the loss of
its only money-making property, the Czech station TV Nova, and the
merger has been thrown into doubt.
</P>
