<P>
   NY-NOMAD (New York) _ The fashionistas are on the move _ this
time to a neighborhood so anonymous it doesn't even have a name. On
the maps in city taxis that show Manhattan neighborhoods _ Chelsea,
Greenwich Village, Upper East Side _ this area is conspicuously
gray. Historical-minded people may refer to it as Rosehill, after
the 18-century farm belonging to John Watts, a Tory sympathizer,
that covered roughly the same acreage. George Trescher, the
fund-raiser, and a local resident, calls it Curry Hill, because of
the many Indian and Bangladesh restaurants. Others call it NoMad,
for north of Madison Square Park. By Elaine Louie.
</P>
