A6360 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-SOC-GALXNOT-LADN-(SLA     08-05 0462
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SOC-GALXNOT-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LOS ANGELES GALAXY NOTEBOOK
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RICHARD GONZALEZ  
 c.1999 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PASADENA, Calif. _ Five games down, five to go.
</P>
<P>
   But while mired in its most grueling stretch of the season _ 10
games in a span of 32 days _ the Galaxy has yet to show any ill
effects.
</P>
<P>
   Credit coach Sigi Schmid's utilization of team depth in helping
his side inch up the Western Conference standings.
</P>
<P>
   The Galaxy, which plays Saturday in San Jose before facing
Columbus in a U.S. Open Cup match at Cal State Fullerton next
Wednesday, sits in third place, a point behind Dallas and eight
behind Colorado.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's going to be very demanding on the players the next couple
of weeks, Schmid said ``Luckily, we have a little bit more depth
than we had at the beginning of the season. Roy Myers has been the
biggest addition. We have the personnel now to be able to adapt in
a number of areas with different combinations.
</P>
<P>
   Schmid is combating the physical demands of the game scheduling
by allowing pared down intensity in the practices while putting
players in the pool to aid in tissue regeneration.
</P>
<P>
   -- Schmid's guess that Mexico's involvement in the
Confederations Cup final on Wednesday night might keep Chivas
supporters away from the Rose Bowl was off mark. When Galaxy
players appeared on field to warm up, an unmistakable chorus of
boos and whistling jeers rained down from the stands. The response
turned to cheers minutes later when Chivas player took the field.
</P>
<P>
   bullet The most entertaining moments to the Chivas-Galaxy clash
were provided by well-known Hispanic comedian Paul Rodriguez.
Appearing at Tuesday's Galaxy practice, Rodriguez took a stab at
Galaxy midfielder's diminituve stature by quipping aloud: ``Hey
Mauricio, you're in the wrong place, man. Santa Anita (and the rest
of the horse racing jockeys) is down the road from here.
</P>
<P>
   Minutes later, Rodriguez lived out his dream in re-enacting a
World Cup moment. With Galaxy keeper Kevin Hartman in goal,
Rodriguez unleashed a penalty kick which successfully found the
left corner. The comedian dropped to his knees in jubilation before
tearing off his uniform topp -- unveiling the black sports bra he
was donning underneath.
</P>
<P>
   __ Doug Logan's ouster as MLS commissioner -- rumored since
season's outset -- was inevitable. But to replace one commissioner
of no soccer background with another of similar lack of expertise?
</P>
<P>
   Don Garber, who was named to the post on Wednesday, is known
more for his marketing expertise while with NFL International than
anything. That being the case, Garber should have been given Randy
Bernstien's job. Bernstein is MLS' reigning Chief Marketing
Officer.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
