<P>
   ATTENTION FASHION EDITORS _ The home and garden survey that the
AJC did in the spring got good use in Dayton and West Palm. Now the
AJC has produced a similar fashion survey that asks questions such
as where do you shop for clothes, how much do you spend and who are
Atlanta's most stylish personalities. If you're interested, the
full-page survey, complete with color illustrations, is available
on the WAN desk of the AJC's database, or via the budget tool. In
Lifestyle category, fashion subcategory, run date Aug. 1.
</P>
<P>
   SCHOOL-FASHION _ Back to school fashion trends. (Moore, Austin
American-Statesman). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   STYLE-FRAGRANCE _ Another in an occasional series of reviews of
new shops around Atlanta. This one's on the super beauty boutique
Sephora at Lenox Square. (Johnson, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   STYLE-SOLARCLOTHES _ Brief story on Solarveil brand clothing and
accessories which are made from a revolutionary sun-blocking fabric
that protects you even if you don't wear sunscreen. (Walton,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS
</P>
<P>
   RACING-EXHIBIT _ GREENSBORO, N.C. _ Visual Arts Review. ``Just
Racin','' an exhibit in Greensboro, N.C., explores cultural
phenomenon of stock-car racing. (Patterson, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 26.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (e) Entertainment and (s) Sports categories.
</P>
<P>
   MUSIC
</P>
<P>
   LEVI _ ATLANTA _ After hearing criticism about not capitalizing
on conductor Yoel Levi's final season, the Atlanta Symphony
Orchestra announces ``A Celebration and Appreciation of Yoel
Levi,'' a series of seven Beethoven concerts for June 2000 that
Levi will conduct. Apparently still smarting over his dismissal,
Levi talks about the programming but declines comment on the ASO's
official gesture of farewell. (Green, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   JAZZ-LALAH _ ATLANTA _ Before she performs with pianist Joe
Sample at Symphony Hall this weekend we talk to vocalist Lalah
Hathaway about the burden of her father's (the late Donny Hathaway)
legacy, the contemporary jazz path she's taken and wanting to
remain a part of R&AMP;B ``even though all it seems to be about, at
least for women anyway, is who shakes their behind the best.''
(SoMurray, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 21.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES
</P>
<P>
   BLAIRWITCH _ ``The Blair Witch Project'' is about to double its
number of theaters nationwide. Here is a look at some of the
weirdness surrounding the film _ like why it was made in
Burkittsville, Md. _ and at the woman who briefly appears in the
movie but to this day cannot be found. (Lonino, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 17.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-IRON _ The Iron Giant is a wonderful mix of traditional
and computerized animation. (Larsen, Dayton Daily News). 15.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-GIANT _ Review of ``Iron Giant,'' an animated film about
a kid and a giant robot from space. Grade: B+. (Ringel, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   GIANT-BIRD _ Interview with director Brad Bird, who breaks the
animated-feature mold of Disney (five songs, wisecracking
sidekicks) to deliver the teriffic, PG-rated Warner Bros. film
``The Iron Giant,'' a movie kids and their parents can like
equally. (Murray, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-SIXTHSENSE _ A review of the eerie new Bruce Willis
movie. (Larsen, Dayton Daily News). 14.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-SIXTH _ Movie review of ``The Sixth Sense.'' (Murray,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-AFFAIR _ A review of ``The Thomas Crown Affair.''
(Luksic, Dayton Daily News).
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-CROWN _ Clever, classy and thoroughly entertaining, this
remake of ``The Thomas Crown Affair'' is one to remember. (Palm
Beach Post). 17.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-THOSCROWN _ A review of ``The Thomas Crown Affair.''
(Murray, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-MYSTERY _ Movie review of ``Mystery Men,'' comic book
heroes played by Ben Stiller and Janeane Garofalo. Grade: C+.
(Murray, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-MINIREVIEWS _ Mini reviews of all currently playing
movies. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-RDP _ Movie review roundup of ``The Ninth Gate'' and
``Dick'' (Which opened Wednesday). (Ringel/Longino, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
