 Here is an updated budget for the Focus and Nascar Pages. Focus
will be available to clients by 2 p.m. Friday August 6, and Nascar
by 5 p.m. August 5, 1999. For questions call CoxNet at (404)
526-5456.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; FOCUS (Available by 2 p.m., Fri., Aug. 6) &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FOCUS INCLUDES SEVERAL COLOR PHOTOS AND TWO COLOR ILLUSTRATIONS
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA ECONOMY: Bank closings. Food shortages. Political
upheaval. Predictions of social unrest. Last Aug. 17, the value of
Russia's national currency plummeted as the country slid headlong
into an economic crisis _ and the world held its breath. But the
crisis did not result in catastrophe. Things aren't much better in
Russia, but they haven't got worse, either. After the heady boom
years of '96 and '97, economic achievement in Russia today is
measured by the bad things that haven't happened. (Includes color
photos.)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: RUSSIA FACTORY: Once the pride of the Soviet Union, the
massive mining and steel works in this Urals mountain city
illustrate Russia's obstacles in competing in the world economy.
Once the world's biggest steel-producing plant, Magnitogorsk's
output is half of what it was a decade ago and quality is low.
(Includes color photos.)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: RUSSIA BOX: Data on the Russian economy.
