UNHOLY WARS - BOOK EXCERPTS To bolster your coverage of the hunt
for Osama bin Laden and the one-year anniversary of the August 7,
1999 bombing of two U.S. embassies in East Africa, The New York
Times Syndicate is offering six excerpts from the book ``Unholy
Wars,'' by John K. Cooley. A veteran foreign correspondent for
ABC-TV News, Cooley has written widely on the Middle East and North
Africa. In 1996 he won the George Polk Memorial Award for more than
40 years of global coverage. He is the author of five other books
on the Middle East, including ``Payback : America's Long War in the
Middle East'' and ``Libyan Sandstorm : Qaddafi's Revolution.'')
Please contact us for more details.
