IDLE THREATS COULD BRING KOREAN DISASTER The noise level about
North Korea is rising ominously again. The focus now is on whether
or not Pyongyang proceeds with another test of its new long-range
three stage missile. Top U.S. officials, including Secretary of
State Madeleine Albright and Defence Secretary William Cohen, have
warned of ``serious consequences'' if it does. The crucial dates
are, apparently August 15 - V-J day of World War II - on which
Korea's independence is celebrated, and September 6, birthdate of
the late Kim Il-Sung and also a big holiday which North Korea likes
to mark with something spectacular. By Flora Lewis. 800 words.
_____________________________________________________________ 4. WE
MAY NEVER HAVE THE 'TRUTH' ABOUT BREAST CANCER Women with breast
cancer, or who are at high risk of developing it, consider the drug
tamoxifen to be a lifesaver. The drug is able to counter the
cancer-promoting effects of the hormone estrogen, which has been
shown to aid the growth of about half of breast cancers. But a new
study has shown how tamoxifen can reverse its colours and stimulate
the growth of cancer cells after two to five years of use. What is
going on is yet another example of the fact that medicine and
science are a work in progress. By Susan Love. New York Times
Op-Ed. 800 words
