Friday. If you have questions, please call Chuck Lewis or Tim
Spence at 202-298-6920.    (The ``HNS'' tag appears in all
sluglines.)   
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-SPYING (Washington) _ The government's investigation into
allegations of Chinese espionage was ``a story of missteps,
miscommunications, misunderstandings and mistakes'' that may have
prevented the FBI from detecting nuclear spies, according to a
congressional report released Thursday. By MARK HELM.
</P>
<P>
   POLITICS (``p'' category)
</P>
<P>
   HILLARY-CLINTON (Tonawanda, N.Y.) _ Hillary Rodham Clinton,
drawing on the nightmare stories of teenagers lives in a nearby
inner city, urges Americans to tune out violent TV programs and
help combat youth violence to transform troubled teenagers into the
productive tax-paying citizens needed to sustain the Social
Security system for the retiring baby boom generation. By STEWART
M. POWELL and DAN FREEDMAN.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ The House Judiciary Committee
recently cleared a measure that would allow television cameras in
federal courtrooms; a similar bill is also pending in the Senate.
This is a good idea long overdue, but judges have been reluctant to
let the sun shine on court proceedings. The biggest holdout is the
U.S. Supreme Court; not one justice wants to let cameras watch them
work. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
