<P>
   FBN-VECSEY-COLUMN (Undated) _ Sports of The Times column:
Something wonderful is about to happen in Cleveland, but it should
be celebrated all over North America. A community is regaining its
beloved football team, which it lost through no fault of its own.
The Cleveland Browns, the real thing, are rising from the ashes of
ownership greed and disloyalty. By George Vecsey.
</P>
<P>
   BBO-MCGWIRE-GWYNN (Undated) _ Baseball has three benchmarks that
it uses to stamp greatness on a player's career. They are 300
victories for a pitcher, 500 home runs for a slugger and 3,000 hits
for an all-around hitter. Tonight, for the first time in baseball's
history, two of those three records could be broken on the same day
in the same ball park. San Diego's Tony Gwynn needs 2 hits to get
to 3,000; the Cardinals' Mark McGwire needs one home run to get to
500. (Game time is 8:10 p.m. EDT.) By Murray Chass.
</P>
<P>
   Sidebars as needed.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-YANKS-MARINERS (Seattle) _ The Yankees begin a four-game
series against the Mariners, at brand-new Safeco Field. By Buster
Olney.
</P>
