<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-05 15:05 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A6859 &Cx1f; tad-z
r d &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FOOD-COOLRECIPES-COX     08-05 0768
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FOOD-COOLRECIPES-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Enjoy these delectable desserts on sultry summer nights
 &HT;    By Jan Norris
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Coconut sorbet with medjool dates, macadamia nut crumble
</P>
<P>
   For the coconut sorbet:
</P>
<P>
   713 1/2-ounce cans of coconut milk (Chaokohor or Taste of Thai)
</P>
<P>
   2.5cups sugar
</P>
<P>
   1tablespoon rum
</P>
<P>
   For crust:
</P>
<P>
   2cups flour
</P>
<P>
   2sticks butter
</P>
<P>
   4ounces cream cheese
</P>
<P>
   For tart:
</P>
<P>
   1/2cup butter
</P>
<P>
   .50cup sugar
</P>
<P>
   1egg
</P>
<P>
   1egg yolk
</P>
<P>
   1cup ground macadamia nuts
</P>
<P>
   2tablespoons flour
</P>
<P>
   2tablespoons rum
</P>
<P>
   For maple creme:
</P>
<P>
   2cups heavy cream
</P>
<P>
   1cup buttermilk
</P>
<P>
   0.25cup maple syrup
</P>
<P>
   For assembling:
</P>
<P>
   2large medjool dates per dish
</P>
<P>
   Bunch of lemon balm or mint
</P>
<P>
   Make the sorbet: Pour all the ingredients in a saucepan.
</P>
<P>
   Simmer for 10 minutes, then let cool.
</P>
<P>
   Pour into a 9-by-13 inch pan.
</P>
<P>
   Cover and freeze overnight.
</P>
<P>
   Make the crust: In a food processor, puree flour, butter and
cream cheese.
</P>
<P>
   It will form a ball. Chill for 1 hour.
</P>
<P>
   Roll out the pastry dough to a 10-inch round.
</P>
<P>
   Leave a 1-inch border all around. Place in tart shell.
</P>
<P>
   For the filling, cream the butter and sugar until light and
fluffy.
</P>
<P>
   Beat in the egg and egg yolk. Stir in the nuts, flour and rum.
</P>
<P>
   Fill the crust with the filling.
</P>
<P>
   Bake at 400(degrees) for 20-25 minutes or until puffed and
golden brown. Let cool; cut into 4-inch rounds.
</P>
<P>
   For the maple creme fraiche: Mix together cream, buttermilk and
syrup.
</P>
<P>
   Heat slowly just until temperature reaches 75(degrees). Leave
overnight in a warm place.
</P>
<P>
   Stir, cover and chill.
</P>
<P>
   To assemble the dessert, place one 4-inch round tart on the
plate. Make a small indentation in the tart and push a sliced date,
standing on end, into the tart. Add 2 or 3 melon-ball scoops of
coconut sorbet to the center of the date, forcing the shape of the
date into petals. Garnish with strawberry tuiles (recipe follows)
and drizzle with the maple creme fraiche. Add a sprig of lemon balm
or mint to finish the dessert.
</P>
<P>
   Makes 4 servings, with leftover coconut sorbet.
</P>
<P>
   Coconut milk pancake with caramelized mangoes
</P>
<P>
   For pancakes:
</P>
<P>
   1cup flour
</P>
<P>
   1teaspoon salt
</P>
<P>
   10ounces coconut milk
</P>
<P>
   1tablespoon honey
</P>
<P>
   1tablespoon vegetable oil
</P>
<P>
   For the caramelized mangoes:
</P>
<P>
   2mangoes, sliced thinly
</P>
<P>
   .50cup honey
</P>
<P>
   .50cup white wine
</P>
<P>
   Mango mascarpone:
</P>
<P>
   1mango
</P>
<P>
   8ounces mascarpone
</P>
<P>
   1tablespoon maple syrup
</P>
<P>
   Mint for garnish
</P>
<P>
   Make the pancakes: Sift flour and salt in a bowl.
</P>
<P>
   Add the milk, honey and oil.
</P>
<P>
   Stir until the batter is smooth. (Add more coconut milk if you
want a thinner batter).
</P>
<P>
   Add oil to a crepe pan. Pour 2 tablespoons batter in the pan,
flip when the bottom side is a golden brown.
</P>
<P>
   Keep warm if serving soon, or store in an airtight container
until needed.
</P>
<P>
   To caramelize the mangoes, in a pan, combine mangoes, honey and
white wine. Cook, stirring to saute.
</P>
<P>
   Reduce the liquid to half. Remove from heat; set aside to cool.
</P>
<P>
   To make the mango mascarpone, slice the mango and puree in a
food processor.
</P>
<P>
   In a bowl, combine mango puree, mascarpone and syrup.
</P>
<P>
   Beat until smooth and creamy, but do not overbeat.
</P>
<P>
   To assemble dessert, place pancake on dessert plate; fill with
caramelized mangoes. Roll gently and repeat, making two pancakes
per serving. Top with large dollop of creme fraiche, and sprigs of
mint. If desired, make another layer, stacking second layer of
pancakes cross- wise to the first layer, to form small tower.
</P>
<P>
   Makes 4 servings.
</P>
<P>
   Sweet Endings tropical mango cheesecake
</P>
<P>
   For crust:
</P>
<P>
   12ounces graham crumbs
</P>
<P>
   4ounces butter
</P>
<P>
   1tablespoon sugar
</P>
<P>
   For cheesecake:
</P>
<P>
   3pounds cream cheese
</P>
<P>
   1.5cups sugar
</P>
<P>
   Pinch of salt
</P>
<P>
   1teaspoon vanilla
</P>
<P>
   3tablespoons cornstarch
</P>
<P>
   6eggs
</P>
<P>
   .50pint sour cream
</P>
<P>
   .50pint heavy cream
</P>
<P>
   1lemon rind, grated
</P>
<P>
   3tablespoons mango puree
</P>
<P>
   Preheat oven to 300(degrees).
</P>
<P>
   Make the crust: Mix crust ingredients together.
</P>
<P>
   Press into buttered 10-inch springform pan.
</P>
<P>
   To make the cheesecake: Mix the cream cheese, sugar, salt,
vanilla and cornstarch until blended.
</P>
<P>
   Slowly add the eggs, sour cream, heavy cream, grated rind and
mango puree until blended. (You may add more mango if desired).
</P>
<P>
   Bake for approximately 1 hour and 45 minutes or until bouncy.
</P>
<P>
   Let cool in the oven then refrigerate until cold.
</P>
<P>
   Take out of pan, and if desired, decorate with toasted coconut
pressed to sides.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
