that is, but Hollywood still has a few spooky tricks up its sleeve.
Take ``The Sixth Sense.'' On the surface, it's a bloated, plodding
psychological drama that doesn't get warmed up until it's almost
halfway over. But for the patient viewer, there are some genuine
chills, intense performances and one of the best
rug-yanked-from-under-you endings of the year. By TODD CAMP. Story
has moved in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
