to remove its advertising banners from Los Angeles street-light
poles. The network secured a city permit and paid $46,000 to put
the 2,000 yellow flags on Los Angeles thoroughfares. City officials
issued the approval, apparently in violation of the city's own
policies against commercial ads. By Michael Coit. (Will move in the
``n'' California news file.)
</P>
