morbidly overweight man from his home because he was having
breathing problems. Firefighters say John Swainey, a former talk
show host for KGIL radio station in Glendale, weighs at least 800
pounds. He was too big to fit through doors at Providence St.
Joseph's Hospital in Burbank so firefighters took him onto Los
Angeles County-USC Medical Center. The man is a lawyer who normally
works out of his bed. By Lisa Van Proyen. (Will move in the ``n''
California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   LA-POLICING (Los Angeles) _ Police Chief Bernard C. Parks
strongly defends his decision to put senior lead officers back in
the field, dismissing critics as trying to stop progress. Parks
also denies his department practices racial profiling in traffic
stops, despite complaints from civil rights activists. He spoke at
a hearing on race relations and ethnic relations, where NAACP
representatives acknowledged that the LAPD has improved compared to
a decade ago. By Rick Orlov. (Will move in the ``n'' California
news file.)
