<HEADLINE>


</HEADLINE>
  The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following sports
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Aug. 6 and thereafter. For questions about stories, resends or
inquiries, call Joe Jares at (818) 713-3602. 
 
 
BBN-MILESTN (St. Louis) _ It could be an historic night for
baseball. Playing in the same game at Busch Stadium, Tony Gwynn
could reach 3,000 hits for his career and Mark McGwire could hit
his 500th home run. 
By Bob Keisser/Long Beach Press-Telegram. (Will move on the ``s''
sports file.) 
 
 
BBN-CROUSE-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ On Tony Gwynn. 
By Karen Crouse. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BBN-KEISSER-COLUMN (St. Louis) _ On Tony Gwynn. 
By Bob Keisser/Long Beach Press-Telegram. (Will move on the ``s''
sports file.) 
 
 
BBN-KEISSTV-COLUMN (St. Louis) _ The media attention at milestone
moments like this, as Mark McGwire learned last year and Tony Gwynn
is learning this year, can be suffocating, frustrating and even
damaging. 
By Bob Keisser/Long Beach Press-Telegram 
 
 
BBN-CEDENO (Los Angeles) _ The Los Angeles Dodgers had decided
Roger Cedeno was never going to be an everyday player because he
couldn't put up the numbers. However, with the Mets, he's hitting
.311, has a .405 on-base percentage, has 52 steals in 64 attempts
and 24 of his 93 hits have been for extra bases. 
By Matt McHale. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
BBN-DODGERS (Houston) _ Los Angeles Dodgers lose at Houston. 
By Brian Dohn. (Will move on the ``s'' sports file.) 
 
 
