 Thursday, Aug. 5, 1999
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Hearst News Service has filed this additional story for
Friday in the ``a'' category:
</P>
<P>
   GENOCIDE-MINISTER (Laredo, Texas) _ A federal appeals court
rules that a former minister accused of genocide in his native
Rwanda may be extradited to face charges before an international
war crimes tribunal. Elizaphan Ntakirutimana is accused of leading
attackers in a April 1994 rampage that killed dozens of people who
were hiding in his church. By DANE SCHILLER. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   The Hearst News Service/Washington
</P>
