<HEADLINE>
FATHERS KNOW BEST
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   Brazilian model  &UR; Luciana Morad &LR; , 29, whose child was proven via
blood test last month to be the offspring of  &UR; Mick Jagger &LR; , told
the British magazine Hello! that the Rolling Stone is a ``loving
father.'' Jagger has yet to lay eyes on his 4-month-old son.
</P>
<P>
   ``Mick is a very decent man, and he loves all his children,''
said Morad. ``He does not blame Lucas for being born. He is a very
loving father and, as fathers go, Lucas couldn't be luckier.''
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, the New York Daily News got hold of a 1998 videotape
of a family visit to  &UR; John Gotti &LR;  in prison in Marion, Ill. At one
point, a young grandson all dressed up comes into the visitor's
cubicle to say hello.
</P>
<P>
   They talk a bit, then Gotti suggests that the boy might become a
lawyer. He'd rather be a professional athlete, the boy tells his
grandfather.
</P>
<P>
   ``To be a good basketball player or baseball player, first of
all, you got to be a good liar,'' says Gotti. ``A good lowlife and
an imbecile.'' The boy is seen to squirm in his chair. ``And you
got to take steroids,'' Gramps continues. ``You must take steroids,
and anybody who takes steroids is a garbage pail.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Fine,'' says the boy, ``then I will be a crook.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't care if you'll be nothing!'' Gotti snaps. ``You think
you're being ... spiteful with me?'' Gotti threatens to beat up his
grandson, then says, ``I know how to raise children. ... You ain't
doing me no favor coming to see me talking sass to me.''
</P>
<P>
   After raging a bit more, he tells the kid to get out.
</P>
