   ``I froze at the bedroom door and started screaming,'' wrote
Williams, who was Hollywood's glamorous water nymph at the time,
1959. ``I couldn't stop myself. ... Jeff was standing in the middle
of the bedroom in a red wig, a flowered chiffon dress, expensive
high-heeled shoes and lots of makeup. I just kept screaming.''
</P>
<P>
   Williams said that Chandler, who thought his fondness for
cross-dressing was the result of his father abandoning him and his
mother hating men, was getting counseling from a cross-dressing
therapist. Williams ended the relationship the day after she saw
him in drag.
