<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TIMES-APPOINT-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TIMES APPOINTS EDITOR FOR WEEK IN REVIEW 
</HEADLINE>
   (bl)  
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Susan Chira has been named the editor of the Week in
Review section of The New York Times. The appointment, effective in
October, was announced Thursday by Times executive editor Joseph
Lelyveld.
</P>
<P>
   Ms. Chira, 41, has been deputy foreign editor of The Times since
1997. She was a correspondent in the paper's Tokyo bureau from 1984
to 1988 and chief of that bureau in 1988 and 1989. Upon returning
to the United States, she was national education correspondent.
</P>
<P>
   In 1980, she graduated summa cum laude from Harvard College,
where she was elected to Phi Beta Kappa and was president of The
Harvard Crimson.
</P>
<P>
   She joined The Times shortly after graduating and started her
career with a variety of metropolitan reporting jobs.
</P>
<P>
   She is the author of ``A Mother's Place: Choosing Work and
Family Without Guilt or Blame,'' published by HarperCollins.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
