<HEADLINE>
TWO EXECUTIVE APPOINTMENTS MADE AT NEW YORK TIMES CO. 
</HEADLINE>
   (bl)  
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Alyse Myers, vice president for promotion and
marketing communications at The New York Times, has been promoted
to vice president for marketing services, effective immediately.
The announcement was made by Janet L. Robinson, president and
general manager of the newspaper, to whom she reports.
</P>
<P>
   In her new role, Ms. Myers will be involved in strategic
planning with a focus on brand positioning and development. She
will also continue to be responsible for all promotion and
marketing communications for the newspaper.
</P>
<P>
   Additionally, she will continue to oversee community affairs,
event coordinating, creative services, special sections,
advertising for the paper and the New York Times speakers bureau.
</P>
<P>
   Ms. Myers, 43, joined The Times in August 1979 as a telephone
solicitor in the advertising department. She graduated from Queens
College in 1978.
</P>
<P>
   The Times also named Christopher D. Neimeth senior vice
president for business development and strategic planning of its
new Internet division, Times Company Digital. Neimeth had been
group vice president of The New York Times Electronic Media Co.
</P>
<P>
   Before joining The Times Co. in 1996, he was a co-founder of
Grey Interactive, a unit of Grey Advertising. His was among eight
appointments made recently to the management team of Times Company
Digital.
</P>
</TEXT>
